  "prompt": "What are the best book in preparation for bank exams?",
  "response": "Preparing for bank exams typically requires a structured approach and the right resources. Here are some of the best books across different subjects commonly tested in bank exams:\n\n### Numerical Ability and Arithmetic:\n1. **\u201cQuantitative Aptitude for Competitive Examinations\u201d by R.S. Aggarwal**\n2. **\u201cFast Track Objective Arithmetic\u201d by Rajesh Kumar**\n3. **\u201cQuantitative Aptitude\u201d by Abhijit Guha**\n\n### Reasoning Ability:\n1. **\u201cA Modern Approach to Verbal & Non-Verbal Reasoning\u201d by R.S. Aggarwal**\n2. **\u201cReasoning Ability for Competitive Exams\u201d by Arun Sharma**\n3. **\u201cAnalytical Reasoning\u201d by M.K. Pandey**\n\n### English Language:\n1. **\u201cObjective General English\u201d by S.P. Bakshi (Arihant)**\n2. **\u201cWren and Martin\u2019s High School English Grammar and Composition\u201d**\n3. **\u201cEnglish for Banking and Financial Services\u201d by A. D. Kumar**\n\n### General Awareness:\n1. **\u201cGeneral Knowledge\u201d by Lucent**\n2. **\u201cBanking Awareness\u201d by K. S. Suresh**\n3. **\u201cStatic General Knowledge\u201d by S. Kumar**\n\n### Computer Knowledge:\n1. **\u201cComputer Awareness\u201d by Sumita Arora**\n2. **\u201cObjective Computer Awareness\u201d by Chandresh Agrawal**\n3. **\u201cComputer Fundamentals\u201d by Pradeep Kumar**\n\n### Current Affairs:\n1. **\u201cPratiyogita Darpan\u201d (monthly magazine)**\n2. **\u201cBanking Services Chronicle\u201d (monthly magazine)**\n3. **Online resources, newspaper articles, and current affairs apps**\n\n### Full-length Mock Tests and Practice Papers:\n1. **\u201cBank PO and Clerk Solved Papers\u201d series by Disha Publications or Arihant**\n2. **Online platforms (e.g., Testbook, Oliveboard, GradeUp) for mock tests and quizzes**\n\n### Combined Preparation Books:\n1. **\u201cBanking Exams: Guide for the Bank PO, Clerk Exams\u201d by G.K. Publications**\n2. **\u201cBank PO by Kiran Prakashan\u201d**\n\n### Tips:\n- Ensure you choose books with updated content, especially for current affairs and banking awareness sections.\n- Integrate online resources and apps for quizzes and mock tests at regular intervals to assess your progress and readiness.\n\nBefore you start, always check the latest exam pattern and syllabus for the specific bank exam you are targeting, as it can change over time. Good luck with your preparation!",
